caption: The image illustrates the magnetic field lines around a rectangular current-carrying conductor. The conductor is shown with a blue gradient, indicating the flow of current (I) through it. Magnetic field lines (B) are depicted as curved arrows surrounding the conductor, showing how they emerge from one side and re-enter on the opposite side, forming closed loops. The axis of the conductor is marked, and two points labeled 'i' and 'ii' indicate specific locations where the magnetic field can be analyzed. The direction of the current is indicated by arrows along the conductor.
key_elements: Points i and ii for analysis
